(126, 32818, '', 20, 'I\'ve got to keep breathing. It\'ll be my worst business mistake if I don\'t.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:04'),
(127, 65267, '', 20, 'A live concert to me is exciting because of all the electricity that is generated in the crowd and on stage. It\'s my favorite part of the business, live concerts.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:04'),
(128, 79258, '', 20, 'There is nothing more requisite in business than despatch.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:04'),
(129, 12343, '', 20, 'Every business and every product has risks. You can\'t get around it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:04'),
(130, 40470, '', 20, 'It is the artist\'s business to create sunshine when the sun fails.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:04'),
(131, 2368, '', 20, 'I do not regret one professional enemy I have made. Any actor who doesn\'t dare to make an enemy should get out of the business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(132, 17233, '', 20, 'Follow sound business trends, not fashion trends.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(133, 58383, '', 20, 'That\'s what show business is, sincere insincerity.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(134, 84550, '', 20, 'Part of show business is magic. You don\'t know how it happens.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(135, 36337, '', 20, 'In the modern world of business, it is useless to be a creative, original thinker unless you can also sell what you create.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(136, 89421, '', 20, 'Understand why casinos and racetracks stay in business - the gambler always loses over the long term.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(137, 4945, '', 20, 'The common question that gets asked in business is, \'why?\' That\'s a good question, but an equally valid question is, \'why not?\'', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(138, 86151, '', 20, 'Commitments are one of the worst things to have in the music business. They\'re very annoying.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(139, 59843, '', 20, 'A merchant who approaches business with the idea of serving the public well has nothing to fear from the competition.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(140, 25890, '', 20, 'If you deprive yourself of outsourcing and your competitors do not, you\'re putting yourself out of business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(141, 61611, '', 20, 'Short cycle business are being impacted by credit, and are being impacted by gasoline prices, food, distribution businesses, chemical business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(142, 68030, '', 20, 'I think we have to notice that the business processes we use right now for thinking and planning and budgeting and strategy are all delivered on very tight agendas.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(143, 62522, '', 20, 'The whole business is built on ego, vanity, self-satisfaction, and it\'s total crap to pretend it\'s not.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(144, 69523, '', 20, 'Half the time men think they are talking business, they are wasting time.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(145, 15676, '', 20, 'Music and the music business are two different things.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(146, 32411, '', 20, 'There\'s no business like show business, but there are several businesses like accounting.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(147, 53975, '', 20, 'Interior design is a business of trust.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(148, 38159, '', 20, 'I\'m in a business where no one cares about anything except how well your last collection sold.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(149, 84750, '', 20, 'When I started the business, I hardly went home. I became very driven about work and about my career.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(150, 37998, '', 20, 'I think it is an immutable law in business that words are words, explanations are explanations, promises are promises - but only performance is reality.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(151, 25750, '', 20, 'In business, words are words explanations are explanations, promises are promises, but only performance is reality.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(152, 83795, '', 20, 'Diplomats make it their business to conceal the facts.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(153, 43238, '', 20, 'It is rare to find a business partner who is selfless. If you are lucky it happens once in a lifetime.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(154, 72213, '', 20, 'You wouldn\'t want to be called a sell-out by selling a product. Selling out was frowned on, whereas now you can major in it at business school.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(155, 50507, '', 20, 'Don\'t think of yourself as a woman in business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(156, 26554, '', 20, 'Had anyone told me that I was going to have a career in business, I would have said, \'No way.\'', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(157, 5244, '', 20, 'You know, every family and every business in California knows what it means to go through tough times.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(158, 68556, '', 20, 'Treaties, agreements and organizations to help settle disputes may be necessary, but they often favor the interests of business over citizens.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(159, 93577, '', 20, 'You shouldn\'t be in the music business if you\'re posing.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(160, 84490, '', 20, 'I\'m not saying I wasn\'t flawed or amateurish. But you can never say I did anything to appease the music business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(161, 48713, '', 20, 'Listen, if there\'s one sure-fire rule that I have learned in this business, it\'s that I don\'t know anything about human nature.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(162, 15607, '', 20, 'Dear, never forget one little point. It\'s my business. You just work here.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(163, 94119, '', 20, 'I\'m no longer dependent on the movie business to make a living. So if I want to make movies as other old guys would play golf, I can.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(164, 79428, '', 20, 'I learned you have to fight for yourself in the picture business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(165, 54144, '', 20, 'As an actress, emotions are my business, my stock-in-trade. As such, I\'ve dealt with them nearly all my life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(166, 25510, '', 20, 'A business like an automobile, has to be driven, in order to get results.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(167, 97051, '', 20, 'Extracting oil from the tar sands is a nasty, polluting, energy-intensive business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(168, 27378, '', 20, 'I challenge you to show me where the saloon has ever helped business, education, church, morals or anything we hold dear.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(169, 50107, '', 20, 'I have been, and will go on, fighting that damnable, dirty, rotten business with all the power at my command.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(170, 93170, '', 20, 'What other people think of me is none of my business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(171, 28210, '', 20, 'Our business in life is not to get ahead of others, but to get ahead of ourselves.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(172, 63084, '', 20, 'The trouble with movies as a business is that it\'s an art, and the trouble with movies as art is that it\'s a business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(173, 85417, '', 20, 'In business, the competition will bite you if you keep running, if you stand still, they will swallow you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(174, 51574, '', 20, 'You can hype a questionable product for a little while, but you\'ll never build an enduring business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(175, 2666, '', 20, 'I am a child but I have to think and act like a woman, this business forces you to.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(176, 16179, '', 20, 'Business ethics has always had problems that are distinct from those of other professions, such as medicine, law, engineering, dentistry, or nursing.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(177, 20295, '', 20, 'Let me remind you that credit is the lifeblood of business, the lifeblood of prices and jobs.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(178, 52460, '', 20, 'I gave up lots of things I love doing: writing, and business, and playing the piano and so on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(179, 44639, '', 20, 'Our company is built on people - those who work for us, and those we do business with.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(180, 44194, '', 20, 'In this business it takes time to be really good - and by that time, you\'re obsolete.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(181, 3669, '', 20, 'A lot of people say I\'d miss show business if I quit. I\'d miss some of it. Now it\'s the only life I know.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(182, 24982, '', 20, 'One thing is certain in business. You and everyone around you will make mistakes.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(183, 94489, '', 20, 'My whole family\'s been in the business. My whole family is crazy.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(184, 65662, '', 20, 'Christ would be a national advertiser today, I am sure, as He was a great advertiser in His own day. He thought of His life as business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(185, 39656, '', 20, 'Corporations are not in business to be social-welfare organizations they are there to make money.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(186, 6092, '', 20, 'I have made some of the best friends that I\'ve got in this business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(187, 56756, '', 20, 'It is the business of the future to be dangerous and it is among the merits of science that it equips the future for its duties.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(188, 75223, '', 20, 'My curiosity and my appetite for evolving as an actor is one of the main components of me still working today in the business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(189, 803, '', 20, 'The word career is a divisive word. It\'s a word that divides the normal life from business or professional life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(190, 45998, '', 20, 'And I\'m not apolitical - I\'m very specific in my politics. But a lot of the time it\'s nobody\'s business unless you\'re over at my house having dinner.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(191, 42000, '', 20, 'I have pretty thick skin, and I think if you\'re going to be in this business, if you\'re going to be an actor or a writer, you better have a thick skin.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(192, 88638, '', 20, 'Suits are looked at more now as a business thing which is kind of a shame. If you\'re not wearing it just for work, you should try and trick it up a bit.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(193, 29515, '', 20, 'I genuinely believe that if you want to get in the film business, get in the film business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(194, 81936, '', 20, 'My goal in the beginning was to buy my mother a house. Now I realize, okay, if I really focus and become a key player in business, then I can build an empire.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(195, 2586, '', 20, 'Planning cities is a necessary but risky business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(196, 3686, '', 20, 'Environmentalism opposes reckless innovation and makes conservation the central order of business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(197, 28658, '', 20, 'A business like acting is 90% luck. You can be a star one minute and out of work the next.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(198, 27920, '', 20, 'You have a career, and you start as a business person. And you work your way, you reach this peak, and you know the time\'s going to come when you go back down.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(199, 79633, '', 20, 'In principle, there are only three main components of spending that much matter to monetary policy: consumer spending, business investment and exports and trade.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(200, 60875, '', 20, 'My success just evolved from working hard at the business at hand each day.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(201, 95165, '', 20, 'I\'ve learned that life is very tricky business: Each person needs to find what they want to do in life and not be dissuaded when people question them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(202, 92966, '', 20, 'In practice we, in the world, must do business with each other.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(203, 73695, '', 20, 'Living the past is a dull and lonely business looking back strains the neck muscles, causing you to bump into people not going your way.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(204, 12450, '', 20, 'Profits in business always depend on the rate of interest: the higher the interest, the higher the rate of profit required.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(205, 81358, '', 20, 'Up until the Depression, recession had a moral character: it was supposed to purge the body economic of the greed and excess that attends a business expansion.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(206, 62574, '', 20, 'A shady business never yields a sunny life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(207, 26243, '', 20, 'Everybody\'s business is nobody\'s business, and nobody\'s business is my business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(208, 83897, '', 20, 'Except for politics, no business is scrutinized more exhaustively than journalism.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(209, 34370, '', 20, 'I have always maintained that society has no business dictating morality.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(210, 20819, '', 20, 'Business is tough you need tough guys.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(211, 48184, '', 20, 'In this business, if you don\'t pay your debts you\'re finished.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(212, 62732, '', 20, 'My home has always been show business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(213, 53140, '', 20, 'You can be in this business 50 years and still not know anything about it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(214, 45939, '', 20, 'I\'m not really in the excuse business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(215, 24526, '', 20, 'The only thing I fear more than change is no change. The business of being static makes me nuts.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(216, 69379, '', 20, 'Judgment is not my business. Existing is my business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(217, 84079, '', 20, 'Hackers are breaking the systems for profit. Before, it was about intellectual curiosity and pursuit of knowledge and thrill, and now hacking is big business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(218, 1534, '', 20, 'It\'s a real roller-coaster ride if you\'re lucky to have longevity in this business - you have to be able to ride those waves.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(219, 29933, '', 20, 'You have got to have discipline and focus - on the customer and how you run the business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(220, 19868, '', 20, 'A business of high principle generates greater drive and effectiveness because people know that they can do the right thing decisively and with confidence.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(221, 28259, '', 20, 'Well, I was sort of a jack-of-all-trades in show business for a long time. I was a singer and a dancer and then I got a job as an actor.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(222, 45727, '', 20, 'I still work hard to know my business. I\'m continuously looking for ways to improve all my companies, and I\'m always selling. Always.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(223, 71296, '', 20, 'The more you are in this business, the more humbled by it you become.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:05'),
(224, 29204, '', 20, 'You have to have your heart in the business and the business in your heart.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(225, 23671, '', 20, 'I\'ve always been able to keep my private life separate from my business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(226, 39684, '', 20, 'My business is the enforcement of the tax laws and the integrity of the tax code and making sure that trustees of charitable giving are true trustees.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(227, 88772, '', 20, 'The goal seems to me at times just to be business first.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(228, 17552, '', 20, 'I\'ve set the model of showing fighters how they should conduct their business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(229, 98851, '', 20, 'You can\'t be halfway in this business. If you don\'t meet the fans, you lose all you\'ve got.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(230, 91623, '', 20, 'Sometimes I think our problems are made worse by the kind of business we\'re in. Playing these road shows is a weird experience.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(231, 86872, '', 20, 'The business is a very tricky obstacle course, and you should be very clear about work begetting work. If you\'re not working, you\'re not interesting.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(232, 98292, '', 20, 'You cannot run a business, or anything else, on a theory.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(233, 36476, '', 20, 'I just make it my business to get along with people so I can have fun. It\'s that simple.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(234, 37646, '', 20, 'I\'m in the acting business. That\'s the ego business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(235, 12474, '', 20, 'I stayed in show business to pay for my animal business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(236, 78864, '', 20, 'Even if the chef has a good business head, his focus should be behind kitchen doors. A business partner should take care of everything in front of the kitchen doors.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(237, 68882, '', 20, 'The Golden Rule finds no limit of application in business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(238, 43399, '', 20, 'Rock stars get room keys, I get business cards.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(239, 99734, '', 20, 'The nature of motion capture is only going to work for certain films. It\'s not going to put any other type of movies out of business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(240, 78347, '', 20, 'Let me tell you quite bluntly that this king business has given me personally nothing but headaches.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(241, 66758, '', 20, 'I think any opportunity you have to be green, whether it\'s in business or in everyday life, you should take it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(242, 16622, '', 20, 'There\'s not a business or a master plan as far as I\'m concerned. I take it week by week, and I don\'t think you ever expect to be able to do the next thing.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(243, 38262, '', 20, 'Politics are about preserving relationships at the end of the day, and it has nothing to do with the greater good for humanity. It\'s just all about business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(244, 77211, '', 20, 'They keep the old business. We keep the ongoing business.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:12:55', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(245, 57355, '', 5, 'Darkness cannot drive out darkness only light can do that. Hate cannot drive out hate only love can do that.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(246, 24364, '', 5, 'The weak can never forgive. Forgiveness is the attribute of the strong.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(247, 15382, '', 5, 'Forgive your enemies, but never forget their names.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(248, 70253, '', 5, 'Mistakes are always forgivable, if one has the courage to admit them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(249, 836, '', 5, 'Always forgive your enemies - nothing annoys them so much.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(250, 68623, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the fragrance that the violet sheds on the heel that has crushed it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(251, 99898, '', 5, 'You will know that forgiveness has begun when you recall those who hurt you and feel the power to wish them well.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(252, 69327, '', 5, 'When you forgive, you in no way change the past - but you sure do change the future.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(253, 12634, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is a virtue of the brave.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(254, 60591, '', 5, 'He that cannot forgive others breaks the bridge over which he must pass himself for every man has need to be forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(255, 63188, '', 5, 'People can be more forgiving than you can imagine. But you have to forgive yourself. Let go of what\'s bitter and move on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(256, 7283, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the final form of love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(257, 88104, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the economy of the heart... forgiveness saves the expense of anger, the cost of hatred, the waste of spirits.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(258, 58284, '', 5, 'To err is human to forgive, divine.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(259, 53164, '', 5, 'To forgive is to set a prisoner free and discover that the prisoner was you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(260, 95906, '', 5, 'Forgotten is forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(261, 42766, '', 5, 'A mistake is always forgivable, rarely excusable and always unacceptable.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(262, 62700, '', 5, 'Forgiveness means letting go of the past.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(263, 48194, '', 5, 'The public is wonderfully tolerant. It forgives everything except genius.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(264, 76828, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the remission of sins. For it is by this that what has been lost, and was found, is saved from being lost again.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(265, 54321, '', 5, 'There is no love without forgiveness, and there is no forgiveness without love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(266, 85999, '', 5, 'If there is something to pardon in everything, there is also something to condemn.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(267, 60394, '', 5, 'The practice of forgiveness is our most important contribution to the healing of the world.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(268, 72701, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the answer to the child\'s dream of a miracle by which what is broken is made whole again, what is soiled is made clean again.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(269, 34996, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is a funny thing. It warms the heart and cools the sting.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(270, 61785, '', 5, 'One forgives to the degree that one loves.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(271, 82706, '', 5, 'To be social is to be forgiving.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(272, 90387, '', 5, 'Man has two great spiritual needs. One is for forgiveness. The other is for goodness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(273, 49096, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is a gift you give yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(274, 8462, '', 5, 'Forgive yourself for your faults and your mistakes and move on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(275, 58465, '', 5, 'Once a woman has forgiven her man, she must not reheat his sins for breakfast.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(276, 71572, '', 5, 'When women love us, they forgive us everything, even our crimes when they do not love us, they give us credit for nothing, not even our virtues.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(277, 28874, '', 5, 'It is easier to forgive an enemy than to forgive a friend.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(278, 7105, '', 5, 'Selfishness must always be forgiven you know, because there is no hope of a cure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(279, 53042, '', 5, 'It takes one person to forgive, it takes two people to be reunited.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(280, 77096, '', 5, 'There is no revenge so complete as forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(281, 87402, '', 5, 'Without forgiveness, there\'s no future.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(282, 52682, '', 5, 'Genuine forgiveness does not deny anger but faces it head-on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(283, 23715, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the key to action and freedom.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(284, 15435, '', 5, 'Forgive, son men are men they needs must err.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(285, 16030, '', 5, 'How unhappy is he who cannot forgive himself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(286, 63971, '', 5, 'Forgive many things in others nothing in yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(287, 97610, '', 5, 'My desire is to be a forgiving, non-judgmental person.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(288, 66511, '', 5, 'The ability to forgive is one of man\'s greatest achievements.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(289, 93470, '', 5, 'Life is an adventure in forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06');
INSERT INTO `quotes` (`id`, `order`, `entry_id`, `category_id`, `title`, `author`, `has_notif`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(290, 88899, '', 5, 'It is often easier to ask for forgiveness than to ask for permission.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(291, 98774, '', 5, 'I do not bring forgiveness with me, nor forgetfulness. The only ones who can forgive are dead the living have no right to forget.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(292, 91145, '', 5, 'It is very east to forgive others their mistakes it takes more grit and gumption to forgive them for having witnessed your own.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(293, 49340, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the giving, and so the receiving, of life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(294, 10108, '', 5, 'To understand is to forgive, even oneself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(295, 53680, '', 5, 'It\'s far easier to forgive an enemy after you\'ve got even with him.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(296, 40507, '', 5, 'I shall be an autocrat, that\'s my trade and the good Lord will forgive me, that\'s his.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(297, 28618, '', 5, 'Love is an act of endless forgiveness, a tender look which becomes a habit.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(298, 6779, '', 5, 'Reversing your treatment of the man you have wronged is better than asking his forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(299, 77803, '', 5, 'Acceptance and tolerance and forgiveness, those are life-altering lessons.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(300, 26909, '', 5, 'Anger ventilated often hurries towards forgiveness anger concealed often hardens into revenge.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(301, 44239, '', 5, 'The heart of a mother is a deep abyss at the bottom of which you will always find forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(302, 52589, '', 5, 'Inner peace can be reached only when we practice forgiveness. Forgiveness is letting go of the past, and is therefore the means for correcting our misperceptions.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(303, 40662, '', 5, 'Forgiveness says you are given another chance to make a new beginning.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(304, 76078, '', 5, 'Nothing inspires forgiveness quite like revenge.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(305, 51370, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is an act of the will, and the will can function regardless of the temperature of the heart.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(306, 55416, '', 5, 'Without forgiveness life is governed by... an endless cycle of resentment and retaliation.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(307, 24299, '', 5, 'The first step in forgiveness is the willingness to forgive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(308, 32613, '', 5, 'I believe in the forgiveness of sin and the redemption of ignorance.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(309, 91708, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is about empowering yourself, rather than empowering your past.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(310, 55351, '', 5, 'We think that forgiveness is weakness, but it\'s absolutely not it takes a very strong person to forgive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(311, 99382, '', 5, 'I think the first step is to understand that forgiveness does not exonerate the perpetrator. Forgiveness liberates the victim. It\'s a gift you give yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(312, 50891, '', 5, 'Soon I realized that if beauty equalled forgiveness, I was never going to be forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(313, 56000, '', 5, 'Forgiveness to the injured does belong but they ne\'er pardon who have done wrong.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(314, 78698, '', 5, 'We win by tenderness. We conquer by forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(315, 84537, '', 5, 'I find forgiveness to be really healthy.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(316, 87907, '', 5, 'My desire is to stand up and brush myself off when I make mistakes and ask for forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(317, 40031, '', 5, 'Forgiveness really is so misunderstood, as well as the power it can release in an individual.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(318, 47812, '', 5, 'I think we learn the most from imperfect relationships - things like forgiveness and compassion.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(319, 20917, '', 5, 'On a level of simple personal survival, understanding and forgiveness are crucial... whether in an intimate personal relationship or on a global level.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:06'),
(320, 54497, '', 5, 'When there\'s that forgiveness present and compassion, it just helps you live so much easier.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(321, 48138, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is indifference. Forgiveness is impossible while love lasts.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(322, 86541, '', 5, 'The world belongs to those who let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(323, 65271, '', 5, 'To let go does not mean to get rid of. To let go means to let be. When we let be with compassion, things come and go on their own.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(324, 37370, '', 5, 'A man is rich in proportion to the number of things he can afford to let alone.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(325, 8855, '', 5, 'Just because something made you happy in the past doesn’t mean you have to keep it forever.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(326, 47792, '', 5, 'Enjoy what you can and ignore the rest. Let’s not waste any energy fighting things that are outside our control.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(327, 86339, '', 5, 'Just keep in mind: the more we value things outside our control, the less control we have.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(328, 78339, '', 5, 'Give up your attachment to having things your way.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(329, 55386, '', 5, 'Sometimes letting things go is an act of far greater power than defending or hanging on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(330, 25842, '', 5, 'Sometimes holding on does more damage than letting go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(331, 95747, '', 5, 'Breathe. Let go. And remind yourself that this very moment is the only one you know you have for sure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(332, 24805, '', 5, 'Courage is the power to let go of the familiar.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(333, 92196, '', 5, 'I realise there’s something incredibly honest about trees in winter, how they’re experts at letting things go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(334, 63835, '', 5, 'The more you let yourself go, the less others let you go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(335, 4871, '', 5, 'The first half of life is devoted to forming a healthy ego, the second half is going inward and letting go of it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(336, 12423, '', 5, 'Let it all go, see what stays.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(337, 25130, '', 5, 'When one door closes, another opens; but we often look so long and so regretfully upon the closed door that we do not see the one which has opened for us.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(338, 21623, '', 5, 'Seek not that the things which happen should happen as you wish; but wish the things which happen to be as they are, and you will have a tranquil flow of life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(339, 97188, '', 5, 'One’s doing well if age improves even slightly one’s capacity to hold on to that vital truism: ‘This too shall pass’.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(340, 48699, '', 5, 'Holding on is believing that there’s only a past; letting go is knowing that there’s a future.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(341, 54420, '', 5, 'Whatever comes, let it come, what stays let stay, what goes let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(342, 6122, '', 5, 'We need to learn to let go as easily as we grasp and we will find our hands full and our minds empty.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(343, 44980, '', 5, 'You don’t need strength to let go of something. What you really need is understanding.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(344, 78987, '', 5, 'People have a hard time letting go of their suffering. Out of a fear of the unknown, they prefer suffering that is familiar.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(345, 35653, '', 5, 'There comes a time in your life when you have to choose to turn the page, write another book or simply close it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(346, 99232, '', 5, 'Once you realize you deserve a bright future, letting go of your dark past is the best choice you will ever make.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(347, 55817, '', 5, 'In the process of letting go you will lose many things from the past, but you will find yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(348, 36003, '', 5, 'Why let go of yesterday? Because yesterday has already let go of you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(349, 82813, '', 5, 'Sometimes you can’t let go of the past without facing it again.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(350, 20342, '', 5, 'One of the happiest moments in life is when you find the courage to let go of what you cannot change.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(351, 70229, '', 5, 'It’s not a matter of letting go – you would if you could. Instead of “Let it go” we should probably say “Let it be.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(352, 73125, '', 5, 'Letting go isn’t a one-time thing, it’s something you have to do every day, over and over again.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(353, 98355, '', 5, 'Time doesn’t heal emotional pain, you need to learn how to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(354, 22803, '', 5, 'The art is not one of forgetting but letting go. And when everything else is gone, you can be rich in loss.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(355, 86935, '', 5, 'Stop acting as if life is a rehearsal. Live this day as if it were your last. The past is over and gone. The future is not guaranteed.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(356, 49533, '', 5, 'Letting go may sound so simple, but rarely is it a one-time thing. Just keep letting go, until one day it’s gone for good.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(357, 77155, '', 5, 'We must be willing to let go of the life we’ve planned, so as to have the life that is waiting for us.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(358, 57201, '', 5, 'Letting go means to come to the realization that some people are a part of your history, but not a part of your destiny.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(359, 69596, '', 5, 'Letting go doesn’t mean that you don’t care about someone anymore. It’s just realizing that the only person you really have control over is yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(360, 4821, '', 5, 'Even as I hold you, I am letting you go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(361, 34689, '', 5, 'Sometimes people come into your life just to teach you how to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(362, 83029, '', 5, 'No drives, no compulsions, no needs, no attractions; when your affairs are under control you are free.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(363, 23491, '', 5, 'Life becomes easier when you learn to accept an apology you never got.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(364, 7532, '', 5, 'Your time is way too valuable to be wasting on people that can’t accept who you are.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(365, 57447, '', 5, 'The most difficult aspect of moving on is accepting that the other person already did.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(366, 39274, '', 5, 'You will evolve past certain people. Let yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(367, 53343, '', 5, 'Some of us think holding on makes us strong but sometimes it is letting go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(368, 31497, '', 5, 'It was strange, really. A couple months ago, I had thought I couldn’t live without him. Apparently, I could.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(369, 60076, '', 5, 'She let him go once. Every day demands that she release him over and over again.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(370, 44496, '', 5, 'I think every girl has that a guy she has trouble letting go of.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(371, 9230, '', 5, 'It’s you who has to hold on to earth. You have to tighten your grip—which means letting go of him.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(372, 7208, '', 5, 'Anything you can’t control is teaching you how to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(373, 68366, '', 5, 'Let reality be reality. Let things flow naturally forward in whatever way they like.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(374, 40562, '', 5, 'You only struggle because you’re ready to grow but aren’t willing to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(375, 11612, '', 5, 'All the art of living lies in a fine mingling of letting go and holding on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(376, 57919, '', 5, 'One of the most courageous decisions you’ll ever make is to finally let go of what is hurting your heart and soul.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(377, 3977, '', 5, 'I demolish my bridges behind me…then there is no choice but to move forward.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(378, 20859, '', 5, 'Let go of becoming but never let go of taking action. Stop expecting and start living.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
(379, 79775, '', 5, 'If you want to fly on the sky, you need to leave the earth. If you want to move forward, you need to let go the past that drags you down.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:29', '2023-01-27 00:30:07'),
