(505, 92582, '', 5, 'I believe forgiveness is the best form of love in any relationship. It takes a strong person to say they’re sorry and an even stronger person to forgive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:08'),
(506, 76714, '', 5, 'Forgotten is forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:08'),
(507, 66107, '', 5, 'Blame keeps wounds open. Only forgiveness heals.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:08'),
(508, 39662, '', 5, 'Before we can forgive one another, we have to understand one another.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:08'),
(509, 72063, '', 5, 'Without forgiveness, life is governed by an endless cycle of resentment and retaliation.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:08'),
(510, 60603, '', 5, 'I think the first step is to understand that forgiveness does not exonerate the perpetrator. Forgiveness liberates the victim. It’s a gift you give yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:08'),
(511, 65370, '', 5, 'The remedy for life’s broken pieces is not classes, workshops, or books. Don’t try to heal the broken pieces. Just forgive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:08'),
(512, 32672, '', 5, 'We may not know how to forgive, and we may not want to forgive; but the very fact we say we are willing to forgive begins the healing practice.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(513, 85144, '', 5, 'When you forgive, you in no way change the past—but you sure do change the future.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(514, 2518, '', 5, 'We ask for forgiveness, and we forgive others who ask us. In that way, we can experience healing, healing in our souls.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(515, 99220, '', 5, 'We are not perfect, forgive others as you would want to be forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(516, 83221, '', 5, 'Let us forgive each other—only then will we live in peace.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(517, 80019, '', 5, 'Forgiveness means giving up all hope for a better past.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(518, 16714, '', 5, 'Real forgiveness is a lifelong commitment. You must practice it every day.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(519, 93555, '', 5, 'He that cannot forgive others breaks the bridge over which he himself must pass if he would ever reach heaven; for everyone has need to be forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(520, 82081, '', 5, 'When you choose to forgive those who have hurt you, you take away their power.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(521, 6056, '', 5, 'When a deep injury is done us, we never recover until we forgive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(522, 66250, '', 5, 'One always begins to forgive a place as soon as it\'s left behind.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(523, 24082, '', 5, 'Forgiveness isn’t approving what happened. It’s choosing to rise above it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(524, 46618, '', 5, 'There are always people who can\'t forgive an able man for differing from them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(525, 80618, '', 5, 'When you forgive, you heal. When you let go, you grow.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(526, 40048, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is a powerful expression of the love within our soul.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(527, 86404, '', 5, 'Because I make mistakes, I know others do too. I\'ve found when I give forgiveness, it\'s me—not the other person—who benefits.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(528, 84716, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the final form of love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(529, 37076, '', 5, 'Though I was unaware of it at the time, that simple act of forgiveness was the beginning of an entirely new level of experiencing life for me.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(530, 45491, '', 5, 'Anger begets more anger, and forgiveness and love lead to more forgiveness and love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(531, 26488, '', 5, 'Acceptance and tolerance and forgiveness; those are life-altering lessons.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(532, 12055, '', 5, 'By having a forgiving attitude, you can change your life and the lives of the people you care about most.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(533, 42026, '', 5, 'One forgives to the degree that one loves.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(534, 96697, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is not something we do for other people. It’s something we do for ourselves to move on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(535, 9475, '', 5, 'Grudges are for those who insist that they are owed something; forgiveness, however, is for those who are substantial enough to move on.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(536, 86156, '', 5, 'A heart filled with anger has no room for love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(537, 12602, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is the key to action and freedom.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(538, 31361, '', 5, 'No matter how much you love someone—the capacity of that love is meaningless if it outweighs your capacity to forgive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(539, 32680, '', 5, 'To forgive is wisdom. To forget is genius. Because it’s true. It’s a new world every heartbeat.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(540, 79443, '', 5, 'But remember that forgiveness too is a power. To beg for it is a power, and to withhold or bestow it is a power, perhaps the greatest.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(541, 39703, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is not about forgetting. It is about letting go of another person’s throat.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(542, 13882, '', 5, 'There is no revenge so complete as forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(543, 51185, '', 5, 'We win by tenderness. We conquer by forgiveness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(544, 54176, '', 5, 'The lesson is that you can still make mistakes and be forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(545, 62623, '', 5, 'You’ll never know how strong your heart is until you learn to forgive who broke it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(546, 48806, '', 5, 'One should never do wrong in return, nor mistreat any man, no matter how one has been mistreated by him.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(547, 48848, '', 5, 'It’s not just other people we need to forgive. We also need to forgive ourselves. For all the things we didn’t do. All the things we should have done.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(548, 63711, '', 5, 'A happy marriage is the union of two good forgivers.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(549, 68158, '', 5, 'I\'m not perfect. Remember that and try to forgive me when I fail you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(550, 8646, '', 5, 'You cannot forgive just once; forgiveness is a daily practice.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(551, 64563, '', 5, 'True forgiveness is not an action after the fact. It is an attitude with which you enter each moment.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(552, 19482, '', 5, 'Forgiveness is a sign that the person who has wronged you means more to you than the wrong they have dealt.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(553, 12325, '', 5, 'A broken friendship that is mended through forgiveness can be even stronger than it once was.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(554, 29123, '', 5, 'Once a woman has forgiven her man, she must not reheat his sins for breakfast.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(555, 16948, '', 5, 'The man who forgives is far stronger than the man who fights.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(556, 31103, '', 5, 'If you can’t forgive and forget, pick one.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(557, 63618, '', 5, 'Forgiveness keeps you from being bound by something the other person might never set right.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(558, 24059, '', 5, 'You don\'t need strength to let go of something. What you really need is understanding.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(559, 75601, '', 5, 'When one forgives, two souls are set free.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(560, 88974, '', 5, 'As long as you don’t forgive, who and whatever it is will occupy a rent-free space in your mind.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(561, 99906, '', 5, 'Most of us can forgive and forget; we just don’t want the other person to forget that we forgave.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(562, 18623, '', 5, 'Dare to live by letting go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(563, 78301, '', 5, 'It hurts letting go to someone you loved but in the end you will realize it was for the best.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(564, 32139, '', 5, 'It’s better to have nobody than to have someone who is half there, or doesn’t want to be there.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(565, 83094, '', 5, 'I demolish my bridges behind me…then there is no choice but to move forward.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(566, 44949, '', 5, 'The beautiful journey of today can only begin when we learn to let go of yesterday.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(567, 3163, '', 5, 'It’s not easy letting go of someone you love. It’s even harder when you know it’s the right thing to do.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(568, 48710, '', 5, 'Letting go isn’t a one-time thing, it’s something you have to do every day, over and over again.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(569, 3903, '', 5, 'Letting go of someone you love is hard, but holding on to someone who doesn’t even feel the same is much harder.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(570, 24246, '', 5, 'I realize there’s something incredibly honest about trees in winter, how they’re experts at letting things go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(571, 11240, '', 5, 'Convince yourself everyday that you are worthy of a good life. Let go of stress, breathe. Stay positive, all is well.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(572, 32639, '', 5, 'The truth was, he now belonged only to my past, and it was time I begin to accept it, as much as it hurt to do so.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(573, 74371, '', 5, 'Letting go means to come to the realization that some people are a part of your history, but not a part of your destiny.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(574, 62050, '', 5, 'Sometimes it takes a heartbreak to shake us awake & help us see we are worth so much more than we’re settling for.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(575, 26623, '', 5, 'You will find that it is necessary to let things go; simply for the reason that they are heavy. So let them go, let go of them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(576, 28298, '', 5, 'If you truly want to be respected by people you love, you must prove to them that you can survive without them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(577, 93732, '', 5, 'There ain’t no way you can hold onto something that wants to go, you understand? You can only love what you got while you got it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(578, 61451, '', 5, 'If you want to fly in the sky, you need to leave the earth. If you want to move forward, you need to let go the past that drags you down.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(579, 57520, '', 5, 'To let go does not mean to get rid of. To let go means to let be. When we let be with compassion, things come and go on their own.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(580, 33765, '', 5, 'If you didn’t love him, this never would have happened. But you did. And accepting that love and everything that followed it is part of letting it go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(581, 82453, '', 5, 'Letting go doesn’t mean that you don’t care about someone anymore. It’s just realizing that the only person you really have control over is yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(582, 90894, '', 5, 'The sooner we heal our traumas, the sooner we liberate ourselves from the people who hurt us. By hating them, we hold onto them. We cannot heal.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(583, 51276, '', 5, 'It’s not easy letting go of someone you love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(584, 69938, '', 5, 'You can only lose what you cling to.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(585, 50319, '', 5, 'Letting go of someone you love is the hardest thing you’ll do.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(586, 74535, '', 5, 'Sooner or later we’ve all got to let go of our past.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09');
INSERT INTO `quotes` (`id`, `order`, `entry_id`, `category_id`, `title`, `author`, `has_notif`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(587, 72187, '', 5, 'When I let go of what I am, I become what I might be.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(588, 8176, '', 5, 'Sometimes, the loudest sound you hear is the sound of letting go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(589, 35328, '', 5, 'Whatever comes, let it come, what stays let stay, what goes let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(590, 56697, '', 5, 'Open your arms to change, but don’t let go of your values.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(591, 46372, '', 5, 'Change can be good but its always tough to let go of the past.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(592, 32613, '', 5, 'Sometimes we have to let go of what killing us, even if it’s killing us to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(593, 41976, '', 5, 'Time doesn’t heal emotional pain, you need to learn how to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(594, 29114, '', 5, 'If we let the storms pass and choose to reflect, we come out better than ever.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(595, 70033, '', 5, 'If you’re brave enough to say goodbye, life will reward you with a new hello.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(596, 67455, '', 5, 'Detachment means letting go and nonattachment means simply letting be.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(597, 74668, '', 5, 'Some of us think holding on makes us strong, but sometimes it is letting go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(598, 9615, '', 5, 'At some point, you have to realize that some people can stay in your heart but not in your life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(599, 36143, '', 5, 'Know that everything is in perfect order whether you understand it or not.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(600, 76094, '', 5, 'Let go of your attachment to being right, and suddenly your mind is more open.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(601, 21256, '', 5, 'We need to learn to let go as easily as we grasp and we will find our hands full and our minds empty.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(602, 78870, '', 5, 'Cry. Forgive. Learn. Move on. Let your tears water the seeds of your future happiness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(603, 40537, '', 5, 'It\'s really hard to let someone go. Especially if that person you’ve always wanted in your life, but that’s the thing.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(604, 56034, '', 5, 'In the process of letting go, you will lose many things from the past, but you will find yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(605, 13173, '', 5, 'It is only through labor and painful effort, by grim energy and resolute courage, that we move on to better things.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(606, 4760, '', 5, 'Holding on is believing that there’s only a past; letting go is knowing that there’s a future.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(607, 16780, '', 5, 'We must be willing to let go of the life we’ve planned, so as to have the life that is waiting for us.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(608, 244, '', 18, 'One of the best times for figuring out who you are & what you really want out of life? Right after a break-up.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-26 19:52:08'),
(609, 72377, '', 5, 'When I let go of what I am, I become what I might be. When I let go of what I have, I receive what I need.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(610, 61732, '', 5, 'Breathe. Let go. And remind yourself that this very moment is the only one you know you have for sure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(611, 38966, '', 5, 'You’ve got to make a conscious choice every day to shed the old – whatever ‘the old’ means for you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(612, 97507, '', 5, 'It’s really hard not letting go of someone you love, but it’s harder getting hurt by knowing the fact that you will never be together.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(613, 4635, '', 5, 'To love and let go, love and let go, love, and let go… it’s the single most important thing we can learn in this lifetime.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(614, 57569, '', 5, 'To let go is to release the images and emotions, the grudges and fears, the clingings and disappointments of the past that bind our spirit.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(615, 50146, '', 5, 'People have a hard time letting go of their suffering. Out of a fear of the unknown, they prefer suffering that is familiar.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(616, 18927, '', 5, 'All that sadness. All that anger. It is the smoke that gets into your eyes. If you do not blow it away, how can you hope to see?', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(617, 79047, '', 5, 'Don’t dwell on what went wrong. Instead, focus on what to do next. Spend your energy moving forward together towards an answer.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(618, 71059, '', 5, 'The day I understood everything, was the day I stopped trying to figure everything out. The day I knew peace was the day I let everything go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:09'),
(619, 50592, '', 5, 'Let go of the battle. Breathe quietly and let it be. Let your body relax and your heart soften. Open to whatever you experience without fighting.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(620, 63218, '', 5, 'It’s not easy letting go of someone you love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(621, 28343, '', 5, 'Pain will leave you, when you let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(622, 50593, '', 5, 'Never be sad for what is over, just be glad it was once yours.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(623, 10998, '', 5, 'Sometimes people come into your life just to teach you how to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(624, 41255, '', 5, 'There is no point in holding on to someone who has already let you go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(625, 16940, '', 5, 'There is love in holding and there is love in letting go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(626, 28272, '', 5, 'Don’t let the heart that didn’t love you, keep you from the one that will.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(627, 45609, '', 5, 'I am not what happened to me, I am what I choose to become.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(628, 40092, '', 5, 'Some think that holding on makes us strong; but sometimes it’s letting go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(629, 46200, '', 5, 'A person who loves you truly will never let you go whatever the situation is.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(630, 35405, '', 5, 'Be strong enough to let go and patient enough to wait for what you deserve.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(631, 54213, '', 5, 'The greatest step towards a life of simplicity is to learn to let go.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(632, 6623, '', 5, 'I know my heart will never be the same but I’m telling myself I’ll be okay.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(633, 87685, '', 5, 'Fall in love with somebody who will never let you go to sleep wondering if you still matter.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(634, 26419, '', 5, 'One of the happiest moments in life is when you find the courage to let go of what you can’t change.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(635, 30234, '', 5, 'In the end, I’d loved him enough to let go. From afar, I would love him forever.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(636, 36470, '', 5, 'Sometimes letting go of the person isn’t enough sometimes you have to let go of your memories with them too.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(637, 21090, '', 5, 'Letting go is a process of releasing something that is precious to you only because it is no longer available to you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(638, 45314, '', 5, 'I mean, I am no love expert, but I’m pretty sure that the dude making you cry every day isn’t your soulmate.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(639, 77885, '', 5, 'The only reason you won’t let go of what is making you sad is because it was the only thing that made you happy.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(640, 89538, '', 5, 'Let go and go beyond living the dream, by dreaming the reality, into a reality beyond the dream.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(641, 46302, '', 5, 'If you love something so much let it go. If it comes back it was meant to be; if it doesn’t it never was.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(642, 10374, '', 5, 'Every time your heart is broken, a doorway cracks open to a world full of new beginnings, new opportunities.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(643, 1723, '', 5, 'Creativity requires the courage to let go of certainties.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(644, 47097, '', 5, 'Breathe. Let go. And remind yourself that this very moment is the only one you know you have for sure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(645, 34142, '', 5, 'We need to learn to let go as easily as we grasp and we will find our hands full and our minds empty.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(646, 38885, '', 5, 'He that cannot forgive others breaks the bridge over which he must pass himself for every man has need to be forgiven.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:30', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(647, 26330, '', 6, 'I can accept failure, everyone fails at something. But I can\'t accept not trying.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(648, 34101, '', 6, 'My great concern is not whether you have failed, but whether you are content with your failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(649, 70133, '', 6, 'Do not fear mistakes. You will know failure. Continue to reach out.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(650, 3413, '', 6, 'Failures are finger posts on the road to achievement.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(651, 71400, '', 6, 'Every adversity, every failure, every heartache carries with it the seed on an equal or greater benefit.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(652, 55516, '', 6, 'It\'s fine to celebrate success but it is more important to heed the lessons of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(653, 52325, '', 6, 'Ambition is the last refuge of the failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(654, 57683, '', 6, 'We have forty million reasons for failure, but not a single excuse.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(655, 263, '', 6, 'If you learn from defeat, you haven\'t really lost.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-26 19:52:08'),
(656, 68098, '', 6, 'A man can fail many times, but he isn\'t a failure until he begins to blame somebody else.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(657, 50389, '', 6, 'Many of life\'s failures are people who did not realize how close they were to success when they gave up.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(658, 21507, '', 6, 'Do not brood over your past mistakes and failures as this will only fill your mind with grief, regret and depression. Do not repeat them in the future.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(659, 33404, '', 6, 'Remember that failure is an event, not a person.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(660, 85387, '', 6, 'You cannot climb the ladder of success dressed in the costume of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(661, 507, '', 6, 'Failure is not fatal, but failure to change might be.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(662, 14783, '', 6, 'Failure is not a single, cataclysmic event. You don\'t fail overnight. Instead, failure is a few errors in judgement, repeated every day.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(663, 59633, '', 6, 'When I was young, I observed that nine out of ten things I did were failures. So I did ten times more work.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(664, 13728, '', 6, 'Success is the result of perfection, hard work, learning from failure, loyalty, and persistence.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(665, 13830, '', 6, 'Failure is a detour, not a dead-end street.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(666, 57261, '', 6, 'There is no failure except in no longer trying.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(667, 74666, '', 6, 'I don\'t believe in failure. It is not failure if you enjoyed the process.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(668, 75225, '', 6, 'There is no such thing as failure. There are only results.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(669, 46077, '', 6, 'If you\'re doing your best, you won\'t have any time to worry about failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(670, 81339, '', 6, 'Success is often achieved by those who don\'t know that failure is inevitable.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(671, 26858, '', 6, 'A failure is not always a mistake, it may simply be the best one can do under the circumstances. The real mistake is to stop trying.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(672, 22341, '', 6, 'If you\'re not failing every now and again, it\'s a sign you\'re not doing anything very innovative.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(673, 91319, '', 6, 'Restlessness is discontent and discontent is the first necessity of progress. Show me a thoroughly satisfied man and I will show you a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(674, 33554, '', 6, 'Achievement is not always success, while reputed failure often is. It is honest endeavor, persistent effort to do the best possible under any and all circumstances.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(675, 77978, '', 6, 'Show me a thoroughly satisfied man and I will show you a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(676, 10189, '', 6, 'I think you can have 10,000 explanations for failure, but no good explanation for success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(677, 89178, '', 6, 'To establish true self-esteem we must concentrate on our successes and forget about the failures and the negatives in our lives.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(678, 5209, '', 6, 'Failure after long perseverance is much grander than never to have a striving good enough to be called a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(679, 47037, '', 6, 'Through perseverance many people win success out of what seemed destined to be certain failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(680, 74240, '', 6, 'Go on failing. Go on. Only next time, try to fail better.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(681, 75300, '', 6, 'Failure is a word unknown to me.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(682, 64628, '', 6, 'Don\'t be afraid of missing opportunities. Behind every failure is an opportunity somebody wishes they had missed.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(683, 34171, '', 6, 'Every failure is a step to success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(684, 37951, '', 6, 'You will be a failure, until you impress the subconscious with the conviction you are a success. This is done by making an affirmation which \'clicks.\'', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(685, 2838, '', 6, 'It\'s best to have failure happen early in life. It wakes up the Phoenix bird in you so you rise from the ashes.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(686, 6666, '', 6, 'The only failure one should fear, is not hugging to the purpose they see as best.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(687, 83666, '', 6, 'There is only one failure in life possible, and that is not to be true to the best one knows.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(688, 63837, '', 6, 'Success is not built on success. It\'s built on failure. It\'s built on frustration. Sometimes its built on catastrophe.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(689, 50196, '', 6, 'For every failure, there\'s an alternative course of action. You just have to find it. When you come to a roadblock, take a detour.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(690, 69730, '', 6, 'Success comes when people act together failure tends to happen alone.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(691, 23151, '', 6, 'They who have conquered doubt and fear have conquered failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(692, 37257, '', 6, 'Do not be embarrassed by your failures, learn from them and start again.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(693, 94862, '', 6, 'The season of failure is the best time for sowing the seeds of success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(694, 10569, '', 6, 'There are some defeats more triumphant than victories.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(695, 37800, '', 6, 'It is wise to keep in mind that neither success nor failure is ever final.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(696, 28767, '', 6, 'All human actions are equivalent... and all are on principle doomed to failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(697, 74206, '', 6, 'Failure happens all the time. It happens every day in practice. What makes you better is how you react to it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(698, 89528, '', 6, 'Indecision and delays are the parents of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(699, 62423, '', 6, 'Do not blame anybody for your mistakes and failures.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(700, 80252, '', 6, 'If at first you don\'t succeed, failure may be your style.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(701, 67797, '', 6, 'Success and failure are equally disastrous.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(702, 36266, '', 6, 'Success isn\'t permanent and failure isn\'t fatal.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(703, 15597, '', 6, 'It is not a disgrace to fail. Failing is one of the greatest arts in the world.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(704, 22284, '', 6, 'Show me a good and gracious loser and I\'ll show you a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(705, 83832, '', 6, 'The great question is not whether you have failed, but whether you are content with failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(706, 37690, '', 6, 'You gotta lose \'em some of the time. When you do, lose \'em right.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(707, 83444, '', 6, 'The only risk of failure is promotion.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(708, 88872, '', 6, 'We climb to heaven most often on the ruins of our cherished plans, finding our failures were successes.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(709, 39428, '', 6, 'Do not let your ambitions become a sanctuary for your failures.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(710, 83543, '', 6, 'A life which does not go into action is a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(711, 40948, '', 6, 'I hate to be a failure. I hate and regret the failure of my marriages. I would gladly give all my millions for just one lasting marital success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(712, 25587, '', 6, 'There could be no honor in a sure success, but much might be wrested from a sure defeat.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:10'),
(713, 68738, '', 6, 'Success represents the 1% of your work which results from the 99% that is called failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(714, 28944, '', 6, 'A hatred of failure has always been part of my nature.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(715, 71429, '', 6, 'Success is never final, but failure can be.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(716, 66387, '', 6, 'Failure is always an option.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(717, 23161, '', 6, 'Success breeds complacency. Complacency breeds failure. Only the paranoid survive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(718, 44171, '', 6, 'Failure to prepare is preparing to fail.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(719, 13256, '', 6, 'Our failings sometimes bind us to one another as closely as could virtue itself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(720, 74961, '', 6, 'Don\'t be afraid of failure be afraid of petty success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(721, 53488, '', 6, 'You always pass failure on your way to success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(722, 10903, '', 6, 'Never walk away from failure. On the contrary, study it carefully and imaginatively for its hidden assets.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(723, 12165, '', 6, 'I never see failure as failure, but only as the game I must play and win.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(724, 50012, '', 6, 'We may be personally defeated, but our principles never!', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(725, 13387, '', 6, 'The world is divided into two categories: failures and unknowns.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(726, 12372, '', 6, 'I have probably purchased fifty \'hot tips\' in my career, maybe even more. When I put them all together, I know I am a net loser.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(727, 50673, '', 6, 'Notice the difference between what happens when a man says to himself, I have failed three times, and what happens when he says, I am a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(728, 19535, '', 6, 'Failure is a word that I simply don\'t accept.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(729, 26973, '', 6, 'The most important of my discoveries have been suggested to me by my failures.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(730, 83245, '', 6, 'Remember the two benefits of failure. First, if you do fail, you learn what doesn\'t work and second, the failure gives you the opportunity to try a new approach.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(731, 59256, '', 6, 'At least I have the modesty to admit that lack of modesty is one of my failings.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(732, 67026, '', 6, 'Before you can win a game, you have to not lose it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(733, 38820, '', 6, 'I wasn\'t afraid to fail. Something good always comes out of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(734, 3853, '', 6, 'Losing is no disgrace if you\'ve given your best.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(735, 50164, '', 6, 'Socialism is a philosophy of failure, the creed of ignorance, and the gospel of envy, its inherent virtue is the equal sharing of misery.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(736, 66321, '', 6, 'In order to succeed, your desire for success should be greater than your fear of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(737, 97127, '', 6, 'Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(738, 48208, '', 6, 'Think twice before you speak, because your words and influence will plant the seed of either success or failure in the mind of another.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(739, 10030, '', 6, 'Success consists of going from failure to failure without loss of enthusiasm.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(740, 30494, '', 6, 'I don\'t know the key to success, but the key to failure is trying to please everybody.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(741, 29278, '', 6, 'Develop success from failures. Discouragement and failure are two of the surest stepping stones to success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(742, 50861, '', 6, 'Failure is simply the opportunity to begin again, this time more intelligently.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(743, 84366, '', 6, 'The only real failure in life is not to be true to the best one knows.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(744, 16557, '', 6, 'There are no secrets to success. It is the result of preparation, hard work, and learning from failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(745, 1143, '', 6, 'I honestly think it is better to be a failure at something you love than to be a success at something you hate.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(746, 228, '', 21, 'Failure is success if we learn from it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-26 19:52:08'),
(747, 33325, '', 6, 'Defeat is not the worst of failures. Not to have tried is the true failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(748, 41230, '', 6, 'A little more persistence, a little more effort, and what seemed hopeless failure may turn to glorious success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(749, 84863, '', 6, 'Success depends upon previous preparation, and without such preparation there is sure to be failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(750, 75588, '', 6, 'A man who has never made a woman angry is a failure in life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(751, 11335, '', 6, 'Failure will never overtake me if my determination to succeed is strong enough.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(752, 34473, '', 6, 'Think like a queen. A queen is not afraid to fail. Failure is another steppingstone to greatness.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(753, 87700, '', 6, 'Socialism in general has a record of failure so blatant that only an intellectual could ignore or evade it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(754, 72220, '', 6, 'Once you start a working on something, don\'t be afraid of failure and don\'t abandon it. People who work sincerely are the happiest.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(755, 9694, '', 6, 'Never fret for an only son, the idea of failure will never occur to him.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(756, 62639, '', 6, 'Most great people have attained their greatest success just one step beyond their greatest failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(757, 61515, '', 6, 'Failure is the key to success each mistake teaches us something.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(758, 46402, '', 6, 'Failure is unimportant. It takes courage to make a fool of yourself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(759, 86422, '', 6, 'My reputation grows with every failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(760, 64341, '', 6, 'Success is never final, failure is never fatal. It\'s courage that counts.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(761, 79951, '', 6, 'A failure is a man who has blundered, but is not able to cash in the experience.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(762, 23506, '', 6, 'Optimism is a kind of heart stimulant - the digitalis of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(763, 10859, '', 6, 'Failure is simply a few errors in judgment, repeated every day.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(764, 78168, '', 6, 'The line between failure and success is so fine that we scarcely know when we pass it: so fine that we are often on the line and do not know it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(765, 91140, '', 6, 'The majority of men meet with failure because of their lack of persistence in creating new plans to take the place of those which fail.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(766, 4513, '', 6, 'No man ever achieved worth-while success who did not, at one time or other, find himself with at least one foot hanging well over the brink of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(767, 44182, '', 6, 'Tragedy in life normally comes with betrayal and compromise, and trading on your integrity and not having dignity in life. That\'s really where failure comes.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(768, 94638, '', 6, 'Failure doesn\'t mean you are a failure it just means you haven\'t succeeded yet.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(769, 18791, '', 6, 'Why should anybody be interested in some old man who was a failure?', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(770, 22301, '', 6, 'Failure comes only when we forget our ideals and objectives and principles.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(771, 84291, '', 6, 'The guns and the bombs, the rockets and the warships, are all symbols of human failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(772, 65211, '', 6, 'In all our deeds, the proper value and respect for time determines success or failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(773, 59958, '', 6, 'A man can get discouraged many times but he is not a failure until he begins to blame somebody else and stops trying.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(774, 23592, '', 6, 'There is no failure except in no longer trying. There is no defeat except from within, no really insurmountable barrier save our own inherent weakness of purpose.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(775, 72601, '', 6, 'Failure is not an option. Everyone has to succeed.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(776, 76016, '', 6, 'Destiny: A tyrant\'s authority for crime and a fool\'s excuse for failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(777, 78697, '', 6, 'Forget about the consequences of failure. Failure is only a temporary change in direction to set you straight for your next success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(778, 94756, '', 6, 'Laziness is a secret ingredient that goes into failure. But it\'s only kept a secret from the person who fails.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(779, 99940, '', 6, 'No man is a failure who is enjoying life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(780, 83104, '', 6, 'If there exists no possibility of failure, then victory is meaningless.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(781, 1709, '', 6, 'I\'d rather be a failure at something I love than a success at something I hate.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(782, 57405, '', 6, 'No man can be a failure if he thinks he\'s a success If he thinks he is a winner, then he is.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(783, 75437, '', 6, 'Failure is not our only punishment for laziness there is also the success of others.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(784, 45564, '', 6, 'I\'m proof against that word failure. I\'ve seen behind it. The only failure a man ought to fear is failure of cleaving to the purpose he sees to be best.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(785, 74125, '', 6, 'All human actions are equivalent and all are on principle doomed to failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(786, 15839, '', 6, 'Ideology, politics and journalism, which luxuriate in failure, are impotent in the face of hope and joy.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(787, 53429, '', 6, 'Not failure, but low aim, is crime.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(788, 40914, '', 6, 'The idea of capitalism is not just success but also the failure that allows success to happen.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(789, 92374, '', 6, 'There are only really a few stories to tell in the end, and betrayal and the failure of love is one of those good stories to tell.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(790, 65866, '', 6, 'To begin to think with purpose, is to enter the ranks of those strong ones who only recognize failure as one of the pathways to attainment.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(791, 20933, '', 6, 'My fault, my failure, is not in the passions I have, but in my lack of control of them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(792, 65431, '', 6, 'Failure is instructive. The person who really thinks learns quite as much from his failures as from his successes.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(793, 27158, '', 6, 'Success or failure in business is caused more by the mental attitude even than by mental capacities.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(794, 96980, '', 6, 'You may have a fresh start any moment you choose, for this thing that we call \'failure\' is not the falling down, but the staying down.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(795, 22840, '', 6, 'He who risks and fails can be forgiven. He who never risks and never fails is a failure in his whole being.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:11'),
(796, 64260, '', 6, 'Big companies are like marching bands. Even if half the band is playing random notes, it still sounds kind of like music. The concealment of failure is built into them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(797, 97235, '', 6, 'A failure establishes only this, that our determination to succeed was not strong enough.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(798, 8903, '', 6, 'One of the reasons people stop learning is that they become less and less willing to risk failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(799, 53194, '', 6, 'Greatly begin. Though thou have time, but for a line, be that sublime. Not failure, but low aim is crime.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(800, 47406, '', 6, 'War remains the decisive human failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(801, 15175, '', 6, 'Failure is only postponed success as long as courage \'coaches\' ambition. The habit of persistence is the habit of victory.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(802, 80630, '', 6, 'However things may seem, no evil thing is success and no good thing is failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(803, 93760, '', 6, 'There is not a fiercer hell than the failure in a great object.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(804, 82085, '', 6, 'Success is not a good teacher, failure makes you humble.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(805, 77469, '', 6, 'Women, like men, should try to do the impossible. And when they fail, their failure should be a challenge to others.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(806, 62151, '', 6, 'The only real failure in life is one not learned from.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(807, 58030, '', 6, 'There is no loneliness greater than the loneliness of a failure. The failure is a stranger in his own house.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(808, 94223, '', 6, 'Keep in mind that neither success nor failure is ever final.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(809, 96652, '', 6, 'I read less and less. I have not forgiven books for their failure to tell me the truth and make me happy.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(810, 71939, '', 6, 'It is often the failure who is the pioneer in new lands, new undertakings, and new forms of expression.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(811, 82004, '', 6, 'Failure is the condiment that gives success its flavor.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(812, 74429, '', 6, 'But while success and failure depend on conditions, the mind neither waxes nor wanes.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(813, 37912, '', 6, 'It\'s not necessary to fear the prospect of failure but to be determined not to fail.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(814, 12240, '', 6, 'Failure means a stripping away of the inessential.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(815, 3340, '', 6, 'Don\'t think of it as failure. Think of it as time-released success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(816, 14799, '', 6, 'Sometimes failure isn\'t an opportunity in disguise, it\'s just you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(817, 30336, '', 6, 'Failure is authentic, and because it\'s authentic, it\'s real and genuine, and because of that, it\'s a pure state of being.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(818, 77750, '', 6, 'Crime and bad lives are the measure of a State\'s failure, all crime in the end is the crime of the community.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(819, 48978, '', 6, 'Whether in success or in failure, I\'m proud of every single movie I\'ve ever directed.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(820, 11540, '', 6, 'Failure has gone to his head.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(821, 52054, '', 6, 'Any critic is entitled to wrong judgments, of course. But certain lapses of judgment indicate the radical failure of an entire sensibility.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(822, 24715, '', 6, 'Belief in the supernatural reflects a failure of the imagination.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(823, 54808, '', 6, 'If a building looks better under construction than it does when finished, then it\'s a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(824, 54587, '', 6, 'Sometimes the best lighting of all is a power failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(825, 8214, '', 6, 'Most success springs from an obstacle or failure. I became a cartoonist largely because I failed in my goal of becoming a successful executive.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(826, 33039, '', 6, 'Young players need freedom of expression to develop as creative players... they should be encouraged to try skills without fear of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(827, 95794, '', 6, 'A real failure does not need an excuse. It is an end in itself.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(828, 83808, '', 6, 'The man who has done his level best... is a success, even though the world may write him down a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(829, 24779, '', 6, 'There is much to be said for failure. It is much more interesting than success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(830, 72390, '', 6, 'You have to be able to accept failure to get better.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(831, 59624, '', 6, 'Success is simply a matter of luck. Ask any failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(832, 60269, '', 6, 'The will to persevere is often the difference between failure and success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(833, 92203, '', 6, 'Failure is simply the non-presence of success. But a fiasco is a disaster of mythic proportions.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(834, 64743, '', 6, 'I believe in trusting men, not only once but twice - in giving a failure another chance.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(835, 62218, '', 6, 'The person interested in success has to learn to view failure as a healthy, inevitable part of the process of getting to the top.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(836, 6815, '', 6, 'Women must try to do things as men have tried. When they fail their failure must be but a challenge to others.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(837, 49513, '', 6, 'If we don\'t succeed we run the risk of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(838, 69467, '', 6, 'I don\'t want the fear of failure to stop me from doing what I really care about.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(839, 25131, '', 6, 'Translation is the art of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(840, 65205, '', 6, 'I\'ve probably earned the right to screw up a few times. I don\'t want the fear of failure to stop me from doing what I really care about.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(841, 16440, '', 6, 'I cannot give you the formula for success, but I can give you the formula for failure - which is: Try to please everybody.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(842, 22374, '', 6, 'We know there is no such thing as freedom without the risk of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(843, 28490, '', 6, 'Heaven knows that I have done all that a mortal could do, to save the people, and the failure was not my fault, but the fault of others.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(844, 73380, '', 6, 'Success is usually the culmination of controlling failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(845, 38185, '', 6, 'There are no mistakes, save one: the failure to learn from a mistake.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(846, 22819, '', 6, 'So many financial dreams are thwarted by the failure to act upon good intentions.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(847, 54889, '', 6, 'A minute\'s success pays the failure of years.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(848, 69678, '', 6, 'Who I am as a guitarist is defined by my failure to become Jimi Hendrix.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(849, 12349, '', 6, 'There\'s no right or wrong, success or failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(850, 12694, '', 6, 'That sense of failure, I don\'t know where people put it who don\'t write songs and aren\'t able to emote physically. It must go somewhere.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(851, 36822, '', 6, 'In politics, what begins in fear usually ends in failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(852, 20691, '', 6, 'I think you have to try and fail, because failure gets you closer to what you\'re good at.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(853, 58976, '', 6, 'Pressure is a word that is misused in our vocabulary. When you start thinking of pressure, it\'s because you\'ve started to think of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(854, 32564, '', 6, 'About the only problem with success is that it does not teach you how to deal with failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(855, 33273, '', 6, 'The main failure of education is that it has not prepared people to comprehend matters concerning human destiny.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(856, 7342, '', 6, 'Success and failure are both part of life. Both are not permanent.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(857, 31473, '', 6, 'I want to swim in both directions at once. Desire success, court failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(858, 49258, '', 6, 'The clearest explanation for the failure of any marriage is that the two people are incompatible that is, that one is male and the other female.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(859, 64976, '', 6, 'Failure is impossible.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(860, 36908, '', 6, 'All war represents a failure of diplomacy.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(861, 62485, '', 6, 'Without failure there is no sweetness in success. There\'s no understanding of it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(862, 33641, '', 6, 'But I look at failure as education. In that respect, I am so well-educated.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(863, 91502, '', 6, 'There is no such thing as darkness only a failure to see.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(864, 54712, '', 6, 'Failure\'s a natural part of life.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(865, 42929, '', 6, 'The exposed nature of life in the public square affects leaders\' attitudes toward risk - and failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(866, 65643, '', 6, 'The only failure is not to try.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(867, 28427, '', 6, 'I\'m sure not afraid of success and I\'ve learned not to be afraid of failure. The only thing I\'m afraid of now is of being someone I don\'t like much.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(868, 30653, '', 6, 'The failure of world leaders to act on the critical issue of global warming is often blamed on economic considerations.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(869, 47974, '', 6, 'Failure is more frequently from want of energy than want of capital.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(870, 18914, '', 6, 'I don\'t understand a way to work other than bold-facedly running towards failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(871, 58607, '', 6, 'We create success or failure on the course primarily by our thoughts.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(872, 20576, '', 6, 'Failure seldom stops you. What stops you is the fear of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(873, 35138, '', 6, 'You\'ll never convince me there is a hopeless situation or there is any finality in any success or any failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(874, 9270, '', 6, 'Failure too is a form of death.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(875, 91099, '', 6, 'Success is more dangerous than failure, the ripples break over a wider coastline.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(876, 5911, '', 6, 'Success needs no explanation. Failure does not have one that matters.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(877, 77414, '', 6, 'Fear of failure has always been my best motivator.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(878, 24895, '', 6, 'It takes two to make a marriage a success and only one to make it a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(879, 4463, '', 6, 'If we don\'t succeed, we run the risk of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(880, 33137, '', 6, 'I may be a successful football player, but I feel like such a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(881, 52704, '', 6, 'I realized that I was afraid to really, really try something, 100%, because I had never reached true failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(882, 54442, '', 6, 'Failure to accord credit to anyone for what he may have done is a great weakness in any man.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:12'),
(883, 49213, '', 6, 'I will not be discouraged by failure I will not be elated by success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(884, 16308, '', 6, 'At first I wasn\'t sure that I had the talent, but I did know I had a fear of failure, and that fear compelled me to fight off anything that might abet it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(885, 89412, '', 6, 'I feel, in the end, as if everything I\'ve done has been a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(886, 24387, '', 6, 'It\'s probably foolish to expect relationships to go on forever and to say that because something only lasts 10 years, it\'s a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(887, 35375, '', 6, 'You can\'t have any successes unless you can accept failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13');
INSERT INTO `quotes` (`id`, `order`, `entry_id`, `category_id`, `title`, `author`, `has_notif`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(888, 11838, '', 6, 'Failure doesn\'t kill you... it increases your desire to make something happen.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(889, 88656, '', 6, 'Failure in the theater is more dramatic and uglier than any other form of writing. It costs so much, you feel so guilty.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(890, 28395, '', 6, 'I\'ve had a lot of success I\'ve had failures, so I learn from the failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(891, 18237, '', 6, 'The most tragic paradox of our time is to be found in the failure of nation-states to recognize the imperatives of internationalism.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(892, 51891, '', 6, 'There\'s a difference between a failure and a fiasco... a fiasco is a disaster of mythic proportions.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(893, 19847, '', 6, 'Rather than viewing a brief relapse back to inactivity as a failure, treat it as a challenge and try to get back on track as soon as possible.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(894, 20735, '', 6, 'If you have a level of expectation in your life that you have to be a quote-unquote star, whatever that means, you might be setting yourself up for failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(895, 38440, '', 6, 'Civilization is a failure. We need to think what we can do together in love and peace.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(896, 27098, '', 6, 'Enjoy failure and learn from it. You can never learn from success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(897, 91146, '', 6, 'Failure is an enigma. You worry about it, and it teaches you something.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(898, 79947, '', 6, 'Even when you have doubts, take that step. Take chances. Mistakes are never a failure - they can be turned into wisdom.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(899, 56069, '', 6, 'If you try to do your best there is no failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(900, 87949, '', 6, 'The failure to read good books both enfeebles the vision and strengthens our most fatal tendency - the belief that the here and now is all there is.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(901, 94758, '', 6, 'It\'s not that we fly by the seat of our pants. We\'re not afraid of failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(902, 11061, '', 6, 'I think success has no rules, but you can learn a great deal from failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(903, 52678, '', 6, 'My biggest failure is I have too many to talk about.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(904, 25786, '', 6, 'Coming to terms with the fact that my marriage was a failure was devastating and very difficult.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(905, 27841, '', 6, 'The man who has won millions at the cost of his conscience is a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(906, 49611, '', 6, 'Even as far back as when I started acting at 14, I know I\'ve never considered failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(907, 6067, '', 6, 'Well, I think it\'s too early to call Fallujah a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(908, 88593, '', 6, 'I\'m fully aware that things that resonate and become real hits are the exception to the rule, so much so that I\'ve wired myself for failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(909, 64100, '', 6, 'We all struggle with our failure to communicate and our failure to reach beyond fear to love people.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(910, 43996, '', 6, 'The failure to dissect the cause of war leaves us open for the next installment.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(911, 36428, '', 6, 'The higher the artist, the fewer the gestures. The fewer the tools, the greater the imagination. The greater the will, the greater the secret failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(912, 34969, '', 6, 'We\'re born with success. It is only others who point out our failures, and what they attribute to us as failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(913, 77664, '', 6, 'The biggest problem in my life is trying to be the kind of man that I want to be, the father that I want to be, and how to process the failure of my marriage.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(914, 36825, '', 6, 'I assume everything I do in life is gonna be a failure, and then if it turns up roses, then I\'m psyched.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(915, 16404, '', 6, 'I was convicted of three misdemeanors of willful failure to file a form.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(916, 90901, '', 6, 'He who has conquered doubt and fear has conquered failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(917, 52283, '', 6, 'Elegance is not a dispensable luxury but a factor that decides between success and failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(918, 99698, '', 6, 'In tennis, it is not the opponent you fear, it is the failure itself, knowing how near you were but just out of reach.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(919, 91684, '', 6, 'When you experience a failure as a leader, don\'t hide it - talk about it. Your missed opportunity will encourage others to take risks.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(920, 82264, '', 6, 'Unwillingness to risk failure is always there, but it gets harder when you feel you have more to lose.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(921, 31255, '', 6, 'Admitting failure is quite cleansing, but never - pleasurable.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(922, 79256, '', 6, 'Once you can accept failure, you can have fun and success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(923, 85391, '', 6, 'I\'ve always believed that it\'s important to show a new look periodically. Predictability can lead to failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(924, 12359, '', 6, 'I\'m not scared of anything in particular, but I am motivated by a fear of failure as opposed to a need to succeed.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(925, 62680, '', 6, 'I failed first grade, which is my biggest problem. You always feel like a failure, like you\'re stupid.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(926, 61496, '', 6, 'My story of success and failure is not just about music and being famous. It\'s about living and loving and trying to find purpose in this crazy world.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(927, 64648, '', 6, 'Failure is the most terrible thing in our business. When we fail, the whole world knows about it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(928, 32079, '', 6, 'Outward failure may be a manifested variant of inward success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(929, 76840, '', 6, 'Of course, Third World leaders love you. By ascribing third world ills to First World sins, you absolve them of blame for their countries\' failure to advance.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(930, 92742, '', 6, 'I didn\'t fear failure. I expected failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(931, 25499, '', 6, 'Schools don\'t really allow failure and yet it\'s a valid part of any endeavour, not just writing.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(932, 59642, '', 6, 'Ambitious failure, magnificent failure, is a very good thing.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(933, 57679, '', 6, 'All I can do will only ever be a faint image of what I see and my success will always be less than my failure or perhaps equal to the failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(934, 66753, '', 6, 'But if you have a solid walk with the Lord, then you won\'t fear that failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(935, 85494, '', 6, 'When you\'re fearless, you take more risks because you\'re less conscious of failure or what can go wrong.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(936, 95356, '', 6, 'The success and the failure are not my concern, but His.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(937, 63619, '', 6, 'We do not realise that we are children of eternity. If we did, then success would be no success, and failure would be no failure to us.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(938, 13118, '', 6, 'Success is not forever and failure isn\'t fatal.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(939, 7166, '', 6, 'How one handles success or failure is determined by their early childhood.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(940, 3780, '', 6, 'Is anarchism possible? The failure of attempts to attain freedom does not mean the cause is lost.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(941, 45449, '', 6, 'When an action is once done, it is right or wrong for ever no accidental failure of its good or evil fruits can possibly alter that.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(942, 15060, '', 6, 'The difference between a beautifully made failure and a beautifully made hit is who you\'ve got playing the leads.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(943, 28718, '', 6, 'If I didn\'t have children, I think my life would be a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(944, 12825, '', 6, 'Every book I\'ve written has been a different attempt to understand something, and the success or failure of the previous one is irrelevant. I write the book I want.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(945, 27021, '', 6, 'I\'m living life as best I can - but I\'m not exempt from failure and making bad choices.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(946, 7133, '', 6, 'Failure, it is thought, is what sells, and what people want to hear and read about. I am not so sure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(947, 42679, '', 6, 'I think I\'ve failed every test I\'ve ever taken. If there was a failure I would have been it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(948, 84044, '', 6, 'I believe only in art and failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(949, 72779, '', 6, 'It\'s not a very high failure rate if you choose people that you really like the sound of.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(950, 47180, '', 6, 'It\'s how you deal with failure that determines how you achieve success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(951, 49572, '', 6, 'It\'s not about failure it\'s about trying something and risking something for attaining your goal.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(952, 916, '', 6, 'Definitely, it\'s a fear of failure that drives me.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(953, 56230, '', 6, 'Sometimes people call me a success for all the reasons that make me think I\'m a failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(954, 92756, '', 6, 'Failure is unfortunately as common as success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(955, 88072, '', 6, 'What we\'ve got here is a failure to communicate.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(956, 7179, '', 6, 'In a crowded marketplace, fitting in is a failure. In a busy marketplace, not standing out is the same as being invisible.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(957, 88238, '', 6, 'I constantly experience failure in that my work is never as good as I want it to be. So I live with failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(958, 29575, '', 6, 'I\'m very comfortable with failure. I\'m very comfortable being the guy who disappoints people.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(959, 57498, '', 6, 'As soon as I did my first five minutes of stand-up I knew that I would rather be a failure at comedy than a success in marketing.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(960, 67360, '', 6, 'Philanthropic colonization is a failure. National colonization will succeed.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(961, 78393, '', 6, 'I think it\'s one of the main negative emotional ingredients that fuels show business, because there\'s so much at stake and the fear of failure looms large.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(962, 98399, '', 6, 'The very reasons sometimes that you make a film are the reasons for its failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(963, 56118, '', 6, 'So I try not to have any actual expectations for myself for any level of success or failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(964, 49991, '', 6, 'A Failure in this Duty did once involve our Nation in all the Horrors of Rebellion and Civil War.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(965, 43359, '', 6, 'Students rarely disappoint teachers who assure them in advance that they are doomed to failure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(966, 69211, '', 6, 'Success is a public affair. Failure is a private funeral.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(967, 55401, '', 6, 'The one phrase you can use is that success has a thousand fathers, and failure is an orphan.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(968, 62812, '', 6, 'One of the biggest problems with the modern feminist movement is its failure to bring men along with us.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(969, 14952, '', 6, 'You can\'t be afraid of failure and you can\'t be afraid of success, because either one gets in the way of your work.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(970, 19711, '', 6, 'I think that failure by your own standards is certainly a form of success.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:13:52', '2023-01-27 00:30:13'),
(971, 48035, '', 18, 'Save a boyfriend for a rainy day - and another, in case it doesn\'t rain.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(972, 16809, '', 18, 'Falling in love and having a relationship are two different things.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(973, 22239, '', 18, 'I don\'t have a girlfriend. But I do know a woman who\'d be mad at me for saying that.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(974, 14554, '', 18, 'Real magic in relationships means an absence of judgment of others.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(975, 14807, '', 18, 'If there hadn\'t been women we\'d still be squatting in a cave eating raw meat, because we made civilization in order to impress our girlfriends.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(976, 11071, '', 18, 'Nothing is perfect. Life is messy. Relationships are complex. Outcomes are uncertain. People are irrational.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(977, 64785, '', 18, 'I\'m not the girl who always has a boyfriend. I\'m the girl who rarely has a boyfriend.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(978, 16655, '', 18, 'There\'s only two people in your life you should lie to... the police and your girlfriend.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(979, 93039, '', 18, 'Smart women love smart men more than smart men love smart women.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(980, 51727, '', 18, 'Assumptions are the termites of relationships.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(981, 59593, '', 18, 'It seems essential, in relationships and all tasks, that we concentrate only on what is most significant and important.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(982, 54200, '', 18, 'A relationship requires a lot of work and commitment.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(983, 52506, '', 18, 'However successful you are, there is no substitute for a close relationship. We all need them.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(984, 13672, '', 18, 'Do not just look at your boyfriend as just a boyfriend. Look at him as a friend, too.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(985, 46929, '', 18, 'Treasure your relationships, not your possessions.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(986, 74496, '', 18, 'Personally, I don\'t like a girlfriend to have a husband. If she\'ll fool her husband, I figure she\'ll fool me.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(987, 50516, '', 18, 'I am a hopeless romantic and I love to spoil my girlfriends.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(988, 98668, '', 18, 'Well, a girlfriend once told me never to fight with anybody you don\'t love.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(989, 51602, '', 18, 'If you can lie, you can act, and if you can lie to crazy girlfriends, you can act under pressure.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(990, 67307, '', 18, 'If you don\'t have a valentine, hang out with your girlfriends, don\'t go looking for someone. When it\'s right, they\'ll come to you.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(991, 71433, '', 18, 'I can\'t even find someone for a platonic relationship, much less the kind where someone wants to see me naked.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(992, 94100, '', 18, 'If you\'re a sports fan you realize that when you meet somebody, like a girlfriend, they kind of have to root for your team. They don\'t have a choice.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(993, 21816, '', 18, 'I suppose I was a little bit of what would be called today a nerd. I didn\'t have girlfriends, and really I wasn\'t a very social boy.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(994, 60036, '', 18, 'Everything I buy is vintage and smells funny. Maybe that\'s why I don\'t have a boyfriend.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(995, 3179, '', 18, 'I\'ve been dating since I was fifteen. I\'m exhausted. Where is he?', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(996, 8321, '', 18, 'I\'ve never been Romeo who meets a girl and falls for her immediately. It\'s been a much slower process for me each time I\'ve gone into a relationship.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(997, 73754, '', 18, 'I change my mind so much I need two boyfriends and a girlfriend.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(998, 50306, '', 18, 'I\'m dating a woman now who, evidently, is unaware of it.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(999, 84831, '', 18, 'I\'ve had enough boyfriends and enough issues. I\'d seen enough train wrecks.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1000, 42891, '', 18, 'If your best friend has stolen your girlfriend, it does become life and death.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1001, 50295, '', 18, 'My boyfriend calls me \'princess\', but I think of myself more along the lines of \'monkey\' and \'retard\'.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1002, 61837, '', 18, 'We are constantly protecting the male ego, and it\'s a disservice to men. If a man has any sensitivity or intelligence, he wants to get the straight scoop from his girlfriend.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1003, 55932, '', 18, 'I love being a single mom. But it\'s definitely different when you\'re dating.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1004, 56559, '', 18, 'I always say now that I\'m in my blonde years. Because since the end of my marriage, all of my girlfriends have been blonde.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1005, 5379, '', 18, 'Maybe the most that you can expect from a relationship that goes bad is to come out of it with a few good songs.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1006, 51252, '', 18, 'Rumors about me? Calista Flockhart, Pam Anderson, and Matt Damon. That\'s who I\'m dating.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1007, 21285, '', 18, 'My girlfriend bought me a down jacket, she said it fit my personality.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1008, 31305, '', 18, 'You show your vulnerability through relationships, and those feelings are your soft spot. You need to have a soft spot.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1009, 77518, '', 18, 'Things were a lot simpler in Detroit. I didn\'t care about anything but boyfriends.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
(1010, 53237, '', 18, 'I have stepped off the relationship scene to come to terms with myself. I have spent most of my adult life being \'someone\'s girlfriend\', and now I am happy being single.', '', 0, 2, '2022-11-25 10:14:18', '2023-01-27 00:30:14'),
